{
  "thought": "First, I need to select the state as California. The current selected option is 'Select state...', so I will change it to 'California (CA)'.",
  "action": "select",
  "ref": 6,
  "value": "California (CA)"
}

{
  "thought": "Now that the state is selected, I need to fill in the full name. I will use 'Jane Doe' as an example.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 14,
  "value": "Jane Doe"
}

{
  "thought": "Next, I need to select the estimated property value. Since the property is valued over $750,000, I will select the 'Over $1,000,000' option.",
  "action": "select",
  "ref": 18,
  "value": "Over $1,000,000"
}

{
  "thought": "All the required fields in the personal information step are now filled. I can proceed to the next step by clicking the 'Next →' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 25
}

{
  "thought": "Since the property needs both earthquake and flood coverage, I should select the 'Premium' plan, which is likely to include these coverages. I will select the 'Premium $200/mo' radio button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 9
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Premium' plan is now selected. I can proceed to the next step by clicking the 'Next →' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 12
}

{
  "thought": "I need to select both earthquake and flood coverage. I will start by checking the 'Earthquake Coverage' checkbox.",
  "action": "check",
  "ref": 6
}

{
  "thought": "Now that 'Earthquake Coverage' is checked, I need to check the 'Flood Coverage' checkbox.",
  "action": "check",
  "ref": 8
}

{
  "thought": "Both 'Earthquake Coverage' and 'Flood Coverage' are now checked. The next step is to select the required 2% catastrophe deductible for high-value California properties.",
  "action": "select",
  "ref": 10,
  "value": "2% deductible"
}

{
  "thought": "The required 2% catastrophe deductible is now selected. I can proceed to the next step by clicking the 'Next →' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 17
}

{
  "thought": "The application details look correct. I need to fill in the beneficiary information before submitting the application. I will start by filling in the 'Beneficiary Name' with 'John Doe'.",
  "action": "fill",
  "ref": 27,
  "value": "John Doe"
}

{
  "thought": "The 'Beneficiary Name' is now filled. Next, I need to select the 'Beneficiary Relation'. I will select 'Spouse' as an example.",
  "action": "select",
  "ref": 31,
  "value": "Spouse"
}

{
  "thought": "The beneficiary information is now complete. I can submit the application by clicking the 'Submit Application' button.",
  "action": "click",
  "ref": 39
}
